Reasoning: This paper discusses the extent to which the web is archived, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely because they deal with the organization and retrieval of web content. cs.WEB (Web Technologies) is also relevant because it deals with the development and maintenance of web archives. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible because they deal with the security and privacy implications of web archiving and the social networks that contribute to web content.
